author: Brian
title: Final practice results for Advance Auto Parts Clash at Daytona
text:
Feb 17, 2017 at 7:40p ET 0Shares 
After two Friday evening practice sessions, Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series drivers and teams have made their final preparations for Saturday nightâ€™s Advance Auto Parts Clash at Daytona International Speedway (8 p.m. ET, FS1). 
Defending Daytona 500 champion Denny Hamlin led an all-Joe Gibbs Racing top four in the final session with a speed of 196.528 miles per hour. 
Rookie driver Daniel Suarez, preparing for his first exhibition race in the No. 19 after taking over for Carl Edwards, was second at 196.279 mph. Kyle Busch, Matt Kenseth and Joey Logano rounded out the top five. 
Alex Bowman, running in his final race in the No. 88 Hendrick Motorsports Chevrolet before Dale Earnhardt Jr. returns to full-time competition, posted the seventh fastest time. 
See below for full final practice results.
